Georges Chamarat https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Georges_Chamarat 0 Georges Chamarat (30 March 1901 – 21 November 1982) was a French actor. He appeared in 109 films and television shows between 1929 and 1981. He starred in the film The Adventures of Arsène Lupin, which was entered into the 7th Berlin International Film Festival.
